cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on semantic labeling in aerial imagery using graph neural networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel architecture that uses learnable latent variables to generate embeddings and construct graphs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new method for automatically constructing graphs without relying on prior knowledge. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses a neural network architecture to optimize the proposed method. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with constructing graphs from visual data.
